Malawi’s Benchmark Tea Price Climbs 28% at Sale Today, Tea Brokers Says

-- B y   F r a n k   J o m o
-- 
2011-06-14T12:25:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/malawi-s-benchmark-tea-price-climbs-28-at-sale-today-tea-brokers-says.html
The benchmark price of tea in
 Malawi ,  Africa ’s largest producer of the crop after  Kenya ,
jumped 28 percent to $2.40 a kilogram (2.2 pounds) at a sale
today, Tea Brokers Central Africa said.  The price rose from $1.88 a kilogram a week earlier, Tea
Brokers, which manages the country’s tea auctions, said in an e-
mailed report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frank Jomo in Blantyre at 
 fjomo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  